    • Method Detail

      • setDatastore

        public VMTypes.StoragePlacementSpec.Builder setDatastore(java.lang.String datastore)
        Datastore on which the virtual machine's configuration state should be stored. This datastore will also be used for any virtual disks that are created as part of the virtual machine creation operation. This property is currently required. In the future, if this property is null, the system will attempt to choose suitable storage for the virtual machine; if storage cannot be chosen, the virtual machine creation operation will fail.
        Parameters:
        datastore - New value for the property. When clients pass a value of this class as a parameter, the property must be an identifier for the resource type: Datastore. When methods return a value of this class as a return value, the property will be an identifier for the resource type: Datastore.
